text: @OOrsak @BantrySeedman @zeefarmer Well we were just talking about expanding a family farm to accommodate the next generation. If you have enough money to start another operation alongside investors why wouldn’t you just use your own money to grow the operation that you own yourself then?

@OOrsak @BantrySeedman @zeefarmer So you would be ok with taking investor money so you could expand your farm and make your kids part of it?  That’s basically like selling part of your farm. You aren’t going to be making the decisions by yourself anymore.
@llay360154171 @KPratchler Yeah you were a little worse. I had my blade down holding the front of the cat out of the mud.
@Denny2point0 @zeefarmer @OOrsak I don’t want you eying up any of our land when you are down here cleaning grain Denny. You stay in your fucking cleaner shack. 🤣
@zeefarmer @OOrsak But they never outbid anybody. 🙄

@OOrsak @BantrySeedman @zeefarmer I don’t think anybody commenting here is trying to say they are special and should be able to buy their neighbours land at a reduced price or given first chance. Just being honest about the future.

@zeefarmer @OOrsak So were they offering the going the price or a little more? And guys don’t think that they will overtake an area. 😂 Once you are stopping by with land purchase contracts you are probably willing to outbid everybody else.

@JBMcAdams @OOrsak I agree but look at the last year or so here when these 20,000+ acre guys sell out. Do they bother trying to piece it out to their neighbours? Haven’t seen it yet. Not to many guys can handle that.
@JBMcAdams @OOrsak They must be paying more then somebody if they are the ones buying the land. How did they buy all that land at LaPas on the auction this past spring? They outbid everybody.🙄
@OOrsak I’m just being honest here. Nothing against anybody.
@MoneoDallas @bigwehrm @Travis_Heide @zeefarmer @Kotyjo Is that in high demand?😂

@OOrsak Bullshit…once they buy a chunk in your area and all the old boys know that they will get top dollar from them guess who they will run to when they want to sell their half section. Money talks most of the time.

@nykoliation @OOrsak That’s a great point. Our little rec hall in Atwater received a grant of over 10 grand to build a deck on the hall from an input supplier based on purchases from local farmers. You lose out on stuff like that.

@OOrsak You are living in wonderland if you think you are going to outbid them on a parcel of land. Once they are in your area they will squeeze you out slowly. You might have enough land now but in 10 years from now if you want to bring kids into your operation you will have to expand.

@OOrsak I’m at the point I don’t give a shit for myself really. I have enough land to keep me happy basicslly. At this point all Monettes are doing is increasing my net worth. But at what point do they start saying what they will pay because there is no competition left for them.

@OOrsak I take it you have come to the conclusion already that none of your kids will want to farm? I’m not complaining, but nobody can compete with these guys and it’s making it that nobody will be able to start farming even if they come from a moderate size farm.
@Denny2point0 @ChadMPetracek That’s the look I get on my face when I rip through a natural gas line or water line in town. Have done both in Atwater where my brother in law is the mayor.
@Travis_Heide I just like calling a spade a spade Travis. It’s funny you haven’t been around here for 2 years but people still talk about you and it’s the same story time after time.

@Travis_Heide I’m not attacking young farmers. You’re older then me. If you had any success’s I could maybe talk about them. Want be to be relevant? I enjoy farming land that got pulled from you by landlords. It’s really pleasing to have the landlords come thank you for cleaning up the land.
